Company Overview of Valued Advisers Trust - Golub Group Equity Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Valued Advisers Trust - Golub Group Equity Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched by Valued Advisers Trust. The fund is managed by Golub Group, LLC. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the value stocks of large-cap companies, with capitalization greater than $10 billion. The fund employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis focusing on factors such as strong cash flow, solid balance sheets, history of consistent profitability, high return on capital, capacity to pay regular dividends, market capitalization, valuation metrics, return metrics, g...
Valued Advisers Trust - Golub Group Equity Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched by Valued Advisers Trust. The fund is managed by Golub Group, LLC. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the value stocks of large-cap companies, with capitalization greater than $10 billion. The fund employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis focusing on factors such as strong cash flow, solid balance sheets, history of consistent profitability, high return on capital, capacity to pay regular dividends, market capitalization, valuation metrics, return metrics, growth characteristics, and financial strength to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the S&P 500 Index. The fund conducts proprietary research to create its portfolio. Valued Advisers Trust - Golub Group Equity Fund was formed on April 1, 2009 and is domiciled in the United States.
